Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Put the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g} and @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} in a small #bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in the @olive oil{2%tsp} for the crumb, then set aside your blue cheese crumb for later.

Halve any large @cauliflower florets{300%g}(halved) and pop them into an #ovenproof dish{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @macaroni{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the saucepan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat the @oil{1 1/2%tsp} for the roux in a saucepan on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, stir in the @plain flour{2%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux! Gradually stir in the @water{250%ml} for the sauce and the @vegetable stock paste{15%g}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the Cheddar cheese to the sauce and stir until melted. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Return the saucepan to low heat and stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat. Stir the roasted cauli and the cooked pasta through the sauce, then pour into the #ovenproof dish{}. Turn your #grill{} on to high.

Sprinkle the blue cheese crumb evenly over the top, then grill the mac and cheese on the top shelf of your oven until the crumb is golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Serve your pasta in #bowls{} with the @sriracha sauce{15%g} drizzled over the top (careful, it's hot - add less if you don't like heat). Enjoy!